SIMPLE: enlarger
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enlarger
<hw>En*lar"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
or that which enlarges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Photography)</fld> <def>an optical device for
making copies of photographs larger than the original, having a head for
holding the original, a source of illumination to project the image, and
a bed for holding the sensitized photographic paper which will received
the larger image.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enlay</ent>⟦br⟧
